ce:section.ce:para:
In this study, an ultrasonic probe (20 KHz; Sonics-VCX130PB) having 3 cm of diameter, was used for extraction of PBPs. 1 g of lyophilized powder of cyanobacterial biomass was taken for UAE. The extraction process was performed for 20 min at room temperature, and the solvent was used 0.05 M of Britton–Robinson buffer. Initially, the various factors were identified in phase I based on their critical role on the extraction of phycobiliproteins (PBPs) under UAE. All the variables were investigated within range, and intrinsic variations within the overall process of extraction do not cover-up the effect of a factor. In the present investigation, solid to liquid ratio, electrical acoustic intensity, duty cycle, and pH were considered for their effect on PBPs extraction. All the parameters were examined at three levels and are given in Table 1
                           . A matrix was planned with the suitable OAs for the designated variables with their corresponding levels. Taguchi methodology offers numerous standard OAs and conforming graphs linearly for this perseverance [24]. Three levels of four parameters (Table 2
                           ) were taken into consideration in the present study, and the number of experiments was signified through a symbolic array of L-9, which includes 9 different trials for an experiment in different combination.
